Apiento, a.k.a Paul Byrne runs the invaluable Test Pressing blog and releases music on World Building, World Unknown and more. His show has that esoteric techno thing and whatever suits the mood…
From the host: "Last show of the year and we have new music from Mad Professor, Emperor Machine, Soos, Persian, LA's DJ Kerry and more…"

nts1.n: LDLDN w/ DJ Gilla (First Word Records)
nts1.d:
LD and guests deliver a slice of realness via jazz, fusion, deep soul, funk, warm techno and the rest. Expect music you can move to from the long-time DJ and producer.
From the host: "This month's show is a bit of a three-parter. The usual mix of new music including a couple of new releases on my Natural Frequency label, a brilliant guest mix from DJ Gilla of First Word Records, and a bunch of non-cheesy music. Something for everyone! Big up everyone who's listened in 2025 x"

From 10 till midnight, Black Impulse’s shows are packed with transatlantic camaraderie and a distortion heavy stroll though metal, noise, gutter garage, trash blues, prog, hardcore, hip-hop, free jazz and anything else.

nts1.n: DIDDY WAH w/ Gabriel Olivier Hernandez
nts1.d:
Adam digs deep into his box of 45s and pulls out a wild selection of 1950s and '60s blues, surf, rockabilly, R&B, gospel, garage, soul and rock'n'roll.
From the host: "Gabriel Olivier Hernandez drops in to talk about launching the new rock'n'roll magazine Human Fly, and to spin some records."
Janie Jones delivers an hour a month of kraut, psych and other treats.
integration sounds from the source; an invitation into the shadow.

LIVE AT THE CLINIC (or LATC for short) is an artist-led initiative founded by shadowy London beatmaker and US Rap collaborator psychedelic ensemble.
Currently, the LATC umbrella includes a record label, and this monthly radio show on NTS, unravelling an hour-long assemblage of grimy instrumentals and edits.

nts1.n: Alice Coltrane Special: Transcending Through Music (R)
nts1.d:
In the immediate years following her husband's death, Alice Coltrane underwent a challenging personal journey, finally emerging from emotional turmoil when she was introduced to guru Swami Satchidananda in the early 1970s. By 1972 she had changed her name to Turiyasangitananda, and left her secular life behind, moving to California. In 1975, she opened the Vedantic Centre.This spiritual awakening would define much of the rest of her life, her music notwithstanding. 
This show explores Alice's later recordings, which are deeply influenced by Hinduism and Eastern spirituality, featuring bhajan chants, and new age influence.
The Cleaners From Venus frontman presents an eclectic mix of pop music, comedy, and more.
Leaf Label A&R and Odda Recordings label owner Thea HD unearths the lesser known common sounds. from old soundtracks, library music to experimental electronic music…
This program is curated by Ondas Representative, Dubby. It features artists, both well-known and unknown, with a unique aesthetic from a wide range of genres that used to be available at Ondas.
Rory Bowens heads The Slip on Sunday mornings every other week - squeezing an hour of hazy dub off-shoots, pupil-dilating shoegaze and uncanny dream music.

Judah's High Hopes explains itself with the name. The blend of soul, experimental hip hop and a range of jazz is enough to bring optimism into any listener's day, and Judah's sonic selections act as a monthly ray of sunshine to brighten any listener's day.

nts2.d: Onotesla (Ono-Tesla tapes) is a Rīga based program that was originally started by Michael Holland and Paddy Shine in the Manchester studios but has since developed a nomadic exploratory based structure highlighting experimental rhythmic based music made mostly by outsiders.

Mexican-American producer, composer and DJ Debit takes over as part of a Modern Love Takeover.
"This show traces how cumbia rebajada shaped a broad field of electronic practice. The slow and pitched down technique that emerged in Monterrey through Sonido Dueñez altered meter, weight and feeling. Its influence surfaces in dub oriented edits, digital and post digital cumbia, regional vaporwave, experimental hybrids and South Texas approaches to edits and appropriations like chopped cumbia and DJ Screw’s fx dialogue with southern hip hop. These forms center time manipulation, bass pressure, repetition and the local tools people use to reshape inherited music. The set moves across multiple regions and roughly a decade of production, showing a magical exchange of methods where the cumbia rhythm becomes a shared terrain for Latin American electronic sound content and form."

Omar Hraib presents The Witching Hour; a passage through the realms of the slow, the heavy and the strange.

Henriette and Catharina of Smerz take over the NTS airwaves once a month with a selection of classical, folk, ambient, pop and more.

nts2.n: The Numero Group - Beyond, the Valley of the Sun (R)
nts2.d: Curated by our colleagues over at Paradise Is A Frequency, this month's roundup introduces you to Numero's latest new age vault of sight and sound: Valley of the Sun. Dick Sutphen developed the Valley of the Sun label to produce at-home hypnosis programs. He directed the content of these recordings to refract New Age’s harmonious, mellow aesthetic and spirit of freedom. To carry out the job of expanding human consciousness for prospective and practicing new agers across the world, Sutphen recruited a crew of unlikely electronic journeymen brought together by cosmic energies and starcrossed circumstances. Like satellites pulled into orbit by the immense gravity of his psychic magnetism, core-producers David Naegele, David Storrs, Steven Cooper, and Robert Slap, would receive Sutphen’s message and mass communicate it back to Earth.

subtle.d: ixxi and Fei take you on a percussive journey with their show syncop8, moving from downtempo ambient to breaks, polyrhythms, and high energy beats, exploring every rhythmic and textural nuance in between.
Representing UK Bass Music Culture across a range of styles, sounds and tempos.

Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!

Darcy is 23 year old DJ from Bristol who specialises in dubstep and grime. With a love for choppy techniques and old school grime cyphers, her sounds create a unique energy that reflect in her sets and mixes. 

New to the scene, she has played alongside 140 legends like Just Jane, White Peach Records, Riz la Teef and more. Working closely with underground labels like Partum Audio, as well as curating a montly show for her residency on Mondo Radio- Darcy continues to develop her style and make her name.

Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.n: Into The Lion's Den w/ Restrikt

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.
